      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HAARACAINE (2) was out of the money two runs back then just missed the frame last start over 2000m at Randwick, beaten 4 lengths into fifth after being in contention on the bend. Perfectly placed in this contest and is sure to take plenty of stopping. WATERMELON (4) finished 4.5 lengths away in fifth last time out over 2000m at Sunshine Coast Poly eight days ago. Steps up in journey today. Should park just off the speed and best figures should see him run well. LET'S DO IT AGAIN (3) progressed nicely last start to finish a close third over 2000m at Sunshine Coast Poly after just missing the placings at the previous appearance. Nicely placed to take this out. BARAZIN (1) has been out of the placings in two runs since a break, the latest when 15th, beaten 11 lengths, over 1600m at Doomben after he settled well back. Third-up record is strong and rates among the main hopes.",
